Sympathy Flowers







William was born on December 26, 1915 and passed away on Monday, February 13, 2012.
William was a resident of Macomb, Illinois at the time of passing.
In 1945 he received an honorable discharge from the U.S. Army.
William was married to Mary.
A funeral mass will be held at 10 AM Saturday February 18, 2012 at St. Paul's Catholic Church in Macomb with Monsignor Richard Pricco officiating. Visitation will be from 6-8 PM Friday at Dodsworth-Piper-Wallen Funeral Home, with a Catholic Wake Service at 8 PM. Burial will be in St. Paul's Cemetery in Macomb.
Memorials may be made to McDonough County Humane Society, St. Paul's Church or Harbor Light Hospice.










