                Submit An Obituary
                
                    




Funeral homes often submit obituaries as a service to the families they are assisting. However, we will be happy to accept obituaries from family members pending proper verification of the death.Submit



































































































































William Lloyd SmithJune 29, 1951 - Dec. 31, 2015William Lloyd Smith, age 64, of Lorena, Texas, formerly of Valley Mills passed away on December 31, 2015. Memorial service will be 11 A.M. on Saturday, January 23, 2016, at the Searsville Country Church near Valley Mills, Texas, under the direction of Foss Funeral Home and Cremation Center. Visitation will be 1 hour prior to the service at the church.Memorials may be made to the "Lloyd Smith Memorial Fund" c/o Jason Smith, 1112 Spring Wood, Robinson, Texas 76706.Lloyd was born on June 29, 1951, in Breckenridge, Texas, to Harl and Alvia (Wampler) Smith. Lloyd was a 1971 graduate of Valley Mills High School and married Florence Smith on June 5, 1971, in Valley Mills. Early in their married life Lloyd and Florence won several dance contests. He had worked on construction of Palo Pinto General Hospital in Mineral Wells. He had worked in the oil fields and at the gas station when gas was 18 cents a gallon. Lloyd was devoted to his family especially his grandson Jeric. He had formerly own Lloyd's Hair Care in different locations around Waco and was currently working at Salon One until he was force to retire due to his health. Lloyd always consider his customers to be family. He was a member of the Valley Mills First Baptist Church. When he lived in Valley Mills, he was very active in the choir and had designed many of their theatrical sets for their programs.Survivors include his wife Florence, a son Jason Smith, a grandson Jeric; 4 brothers; 2 sisters; other closed family; Winnie Smith Stephens, Wayne and Betty Light, Reba and Marvin Yates and his dog Bentley.Please join us in remembering Lloyd by visiting our memorial at www.fossfuneralhome.com.Get Waco Trib headlines in your email, daily — sign up here

























































